  "text": "Data were corrected for background scattering of the buffer after radial averaging. Distance distribution functions, P(r), were obtained by indirect Fourier transform of scattering intensity data using GNOM [CITATION_1] . The best estimate of r max was obtained by fitting the data without constraining P(r max). Next, r max was held constant while varying the regularization parameter (a) to obtain the best least-squares fit to the data that also maximized smoothness constraints. Values of R g obtained from the indirect transform method were more precise and less sensitive to experimental noise than those obtained from the Guinier method. Errors in R g were less than ±1 Å in low [Mg 2+ ] and less than ±0.5 Å in high [Mg 2+ ] in the titration curves.",
